Interface IMySortedMap<K extends java.lang.Comparable<K>,​V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - Generic type representing the keys in this map. Keys must be comparable.
    V - Generic type representing the values in this map.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DLSortedMap
    public interface IMySortedMap<K extends java.lang.Comparable<K>,​V>
    Abstract Data Type representing a type of sorted map. This ADT stores key/value pairs. Keys are unique and can be accessed either in key order or in insertion order. Inserting a key that is already in the map will overwrite the associated value. The "insertion order" is based on the last time a key was put into the map, NOT the first time it was put into the map. Therefore whenever a key/value pair is added using the put(...) method, it will be considered to be the last inserted key. A key/value pair can be removed at any time.

      • getKeysInKeyOrder

        IIterator<K> getKeysInKeyOrder()
        This method allows the keys to be iterated over in ascending order. (i.e. the lowest key should be first and the highest key should be last).
        Returns:
        An dsa.iface.IIterator that allows iteration over the keys in key order.

      • getKeysInInsertionOrder

        IIterator<K> getKeysInInsertionOrder()
        This method allows the keys to be iterated over in insertion order. (i.e. the key that was first inserted into the map should come first, and the key that was most recently inserted into the map should come last).
        Returns:
        An dsa.iface.IIterator that allows iteration over the keys in insertion order.

      • put

        V put​(K key,
      V value)
        Add a new key/value pair to the map. If the key already exists in the map, this method will replace its associated value, and return the value that was replaced. Even if the key was previously in the map, this key is now the most recent key to be inserted into the map.
        Parameters:
        key - The key to add.
        value - The value associated with key.
        Returns:
        The value formerly associated with key, if key was already in the map, null otherwise.
